resources.string: Based in the fast-paced South Mumbai, the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation (BMC) Building is more than just a heritage site, it is a timeless icon that stands tall and resonates a unique charm even today. The foundations of the building are 128 years old, and etched in its walls are countless stories about the vivid past of Mumbai. Thanks to this initiative, you can choose to witness these stories firsthand. The UrbsPrima heritage walk conducted by Khaki Tours offers you the unique opportunity to walk through the historic corridors of this multi-storied building as you learn about the history of Mumbai’s everchanging skylines, the rise of the BMC, and the architectural marvels of the building itself including highlights such as the lions from Italy, the fountain of ducks, and the floating staircase.
